article.headline: UMKC 68, E. Washington 61
article.story: CHENEY, Wash. -- Spencer Johnson had 23 points and 11 rebounds as Missouri-Kansas City handed Eastern Washington its first home loss, 68-61, in a nonconference game on Thursday night. Playing in front of a sparse crowd caused by a record-breaking storm that dumped about two feet of snow in 24 hours, the Kangaroos (5-8) pulled away from the Eagles (6-4) with a 9-0 run in the final two minutes. Bakari Lewis, who added 14 points and eight assists for Missouri-Kansas City, hit two foul shots and sank a short jumper in the final 1:14. Brandon Moore scored 16 points and Andy Genao 14 for Eastern Washington, which managed just one field goal in the final 7:45. Eastern Washington grabbed its biggest lead, 26-17, with 5:35 left in the first half and led until Lewis sank one of two foul shots to give the Kangaroos a 46-45 lead with 11:21 left in the second half.
